Kim Jong Il Gives On-Site Guidance to Pig Farms  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 26 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il gave on-the-spot guidance to the newly built  and reconstructed pig farms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Pak Nam Gi, department director of the Central Committee of the WPK, Ri Yong Chol and Ri Jae Il, first vice-department directors of the C.C., the WPK, and KPA Generals Hyon Chol Hae and Ri Myong Su. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first leg of his guidance was the Sariwon Pig Farm newly built by people in North Hwanghae Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After being briefed on the farm before a huge painting showing the panoramic view of the farm, he went round the outside and inside of the farm to acquaint himself with its construction and management. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He walked round pigsties and the feed processing room and other places of the farm to learn about the technical equipment and the pig breeding there. He expressed satisfaction over the fact that the employees of the farm are devoting their wisdom and enthusiasm to the efforts to increase the supply of pork to people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks to be implemented by the farm, noting that the appearance of one more modern pig farm in Sariwon made it possible to boost the pork production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The next leg of his guidance was the October 7 Pig Farm reconstructed by servicepersons of the KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Looking round the production processes on the farm, Kim Jong Il acquainted himself with the technological updating and pig breeding there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After going round the pig farms, he set forth important tasks which would serve as guidelines for further developing the nation's stockbreeding. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted that to develop stock-breeding is one of the important ways of increasing the supply of meat to the people but also boosting the grain production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that in order to increase the production of pork at the pig farms it is necessary to thoroughly establish a scientific management system based on modern technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The breeding on the chicken farms and pig farms that sprang up in recent years has been put on a scientific basis and this resulted in leaping progress in livestock products, he said, adding that the experience goes to prove that it is possible to bring about a fresh turn in stock-breeding, too, in a brief span of time when the revolutionary spirit and creative ingenuity of people are given full play on the basis of the advantages of Korean-style socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that it is the aim of Korean-style socialism to protect and meet the wishes and interests of the people, he called on all fields and units to wage a dynamic drive to further develop the stock-breeding as a mass movement and thus provide the people with a more affluent and highly civilized life.

Gifts and New Year's Cards to Kim Jong Il from Russian Organizations  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 26 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with gifts and New Year's cards by the State Academy Beryozka Dancing Troupe of Russia Named after N.S.Nadezhdina and the State Academic Moiseyev Dance Company on the occasion of the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and on the occasion of the New Year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were handed to the DPRK ambassador to Russia on Dec. 21 by Tarasov, vice-director of the above-said dancing troupe, and Scherbakova, director of the above-said dance company.

Floral Baskets and Congratulatory Letters to Kim Jong Il from Foreign Diplomats 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 26 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with floral baskets and congratulatory letters by the economic and commercial councilors' corps and officials in charge of cultural and friendly relations of different embassies here on the occasion of the New Year Juche 97 (2008). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The floral baskets and congratulatory letters were separately handed today to officials concerned by Enrique Gomez Soler, commercial councilor of the Cuban embassy here who is doyen of the corps and Muhammad Saeed Khan, councilor of the Pakistani embassy, on behalf of the officials in charge of the above-said relations.

Remains of More Martyrs Buried in Patriotic Martyrs Cemetery  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 26 (KCNA) -- Remains of more martyrs who performed exploits in the sacred struggle to achieve the liberation and prosperity and development of the country and its reunification and accomplish the cause of socialism were buried in the Patriotic Martyrs Cemetery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them were Jong Jun Gi, former vice-premier of the then Administration Council, and Pak Si Hyong who made a signal contribution to the development of the shipbuilding industry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also included Kim Yun Se who participated in the anti-Japanese struggle and laid down his life while courageously struggling to materialize the plan of President Kim Il Sung for national reunification after liberation and General Officers of the Korean People's Army Kang Tok Su, Sim Won Il, Ri Hwal and Kang Thae Mu and Kim Yun Phil, former vice-minister of the then Public Security. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also buried there were remains of Jong So Chon, former director and editor-in-chief of the Literary and Art Publishing House, Kim Chang Ryong, former conductor of the Mansudae Art Troupe, Yu Kyong Ae, former actress of the Radio and TV Broadcasting Committee of the DPRK, O Mi Ran, former actress of the April 25 Film Studio of the KPA, and Jon Kum Son, former newscaster of the committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them were remains of Ri Jong Uk, former director of the then Nose, Ear and Throat Hospital of the Korean Red Cross General Hospital, Kim Rak Je, former researcher of the Microbiological Institute of the Academy of Medical Science, Kim Yu Bong, former coal miner of the February 8 Jikdong Youth Coal Mine, and Pak Jin Sok, former scaffold worker of the Guidance Bureau for the Construction of Revolutionary Sites. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Burial ceremonies took place on Dec. 25 and 26. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the C.C., the Workers' Party of Korea, and officials concerned and their bereaved families. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the ceremonies.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths and bouquets were placed after the burials.

Sports Contest for Osandok Cup Closes 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 26 (KCNA) -- The sports contest for Osandok Cup came to a close after it was opened on Dec. 7 on the occasion of the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Men players of the Sports Group of the Pyongyang Railway Bureau and women players of the Sports Group of Kanggye University of Education No. 1 came first in the ice hockey event. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Players of the Pyongyang Winter Sports Group placed first in the team standing of the figure skating event while men players of the Pyongyang Winter Sports Group and women players of the Jangsan Sports Group emerged winners in the team standing of short track speed skating event. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A closing ceremony took place at the Ice Rink Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, was among those present at the ceremony.

Winter Recreation of Agricultural Working People in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 26 (KCNA) -- Winter recreation of agricultural working people is at its height in the DPRK. A good many people are spending joyful days at the rest homes across the country at state expenses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Those from Jongphyong and Sinhung Counties, South Hamgyong Province, are spending their holidays at the Kobangsan Rest Home in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@They visited the Korean Revolution Museum and went to theaters in the city. Every day they play various amusement and sport games including yut-game, chess and volleyball. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Haksadae, Riwon, Onpho and other rest homes afford all conveniences available so that the holiday-makers from cities and counties in North and South Hamgyong Provinces can have a good time, enjoying colorful cultural and emotional life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@At the Kuam and other rest homes in South Hwanghae Province the holiday-makers go sight-seeing to scenic spots, have meetings for sharing experience on farming and for recounting impressions of books they have read and play volleyball, basketball and table tennis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The holiday homes for the regular rest of farmers open from the beginning of December to next mid-February.

Japan's Move to Become Military Giant under Fire  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 26 (KCNA) -- The Japan Ministry of Defence is now contemplating developing indigenous fighters with a stealth function. Recently MSDF Aegis destroyer "Kongo" shot down a ballistic missile with a "SM-3" in a test, the first of its kind, conducted with the backing of the U.S. naval force. This put Japan's move to establish its own missile defence system for intercepting ballistic missiles by two stages with the help of "PAC-3" already deployed in the U.S. forces base in Japan on the phase of its implementation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today observes in a signed commentary carried in this regard: The Japanese militarists' moves to emerge a military giant are reckless actions to spark a new Cold War and an arms race and increase the danger of war in Northeast Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the strategic scenario and criminal intention of the Japanese reactionaries to realize their ambition for reinvasion without fail by building their own missile shield and holding military supremacy in Asia through positive involvement and cooperation in the U.S. moves to establish the MD. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries have become more frantic in the joint study and development of the missile shield with the U.S. and joint exercises for missile defence recently under the absurd pretext of someone's "missile threat," spending a huge amount of funds for this purpose. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The missile intercepting test conducted by Japan against this backdrop means a new dangerous development in its ambitious bid to build the missile shield and emerge a military giant. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries would be well advised to bear in mind that the hysteria kicked up by them for reinvasion, oblivious of the bitter lesson taught by history, would only bring them horrendous misfortune.

U.S. Persistent Hostile Policy toward DPRK under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 26 (KCNA) -- The whole Korean nation has waged a vigorous struggle to achieve the peace and peaceful reunification of the country this year. Nevertheless, the situation of the Korean Peninsula still remains tense. This is entirely attributable to the U.S. anachronistic hostile policy of aggression toward the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the U.S. policy toward the DPRK, the policy of aggression based on its military power, is the main factor of escalating tension on the Korean Peninsula, the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "RSOI", "Foal Eagle" and "Ulji Focus Lens" joint military exercises staged in south Korea by the U.S. bellicose forces were war moves against the DPRK, which showed that there is no change in the U.S. hostile policy toward the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year the U.S. has sped up arms buildup on a large scale to invade the DPRK, including the introduction into the Korean Peninsula and its surrounding areas of dangerous preemptive nuclear strike means. It is needless to say that such actions are as good as dangerous provocative moves wrecking the atmosphere for peace on the Korean Peninsula and driving the situation to the brink of war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. occupation of south Korea is a vivid manifestation of its hostile policy toward the DPRK and the U.S. imperialist aggression forces in south Korea are an executor for putting into practice this policy of aggression on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has instigated the south Korean warmongers to the confrontation and military actions against the fellow countrymen in a desperate attempt to sow discord among Koreans and check their desire for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has worked hard to further gear the south Korean army to the military vassal system, talking about the south Korea-U.S. "alliance" at such confabs as "annual security meeting" and "security policy initiative meeting". It has also offered the south Korean bellicose forces a huge amount of lethal equipment under the signboard of "cooperation in security" to set them on the confrontation with the fellow countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. bellicose forces' policy of aggression on the DPRK is the root cause of ruining the peace and stability on the Korean Peninsula and a source of aggravation of the tension and outbreak of war.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 26 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today says in a signed article that Kim Jong Il's work "Respecting the Forerunners of the Revolution Is a Noble Moral Obligation of Revolutionaries", published on Dec. 25, Juche 84 (1995), is an immortal library for establishing revolutionary morality in the present times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il is the supreme incarnation of revolutionary moral obligation as no one can match him in this respect and the Korean people deem it immense honor to become his soldiers, attracted by his great personality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people's noble sense of revolutionary moral obligation finds its vivid manifestation in that they are holding President Kim Il Sung in high esteem with intense loyalty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The slogans "The great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung will always be with us" and "Let us arm ourselves more firmly with the revolutionary ideas of the great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung!" serve as the slogans reflecting faith to be always held aloft by the Korean people and all the struggles of the Korean people are oriented to translating the desire of the President into brilliant reality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people's noble sense of revolutionary moral obligation finds its full expression in that they have steadfastly carried forward the ideological and moral legacies bequeathed to them by the revolutionary forerunners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The firm faith in the victory of the revolution, the indomitable fighting spirit, revolutionary optimism and the revolutionary spirit of self-reliance, revolutionary comradeship and burning hatred for enemies and transparent revolutionary principle serve as great mental power for the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is in this noble revolutionary spirit that the Korean people weathered out such ordeals as the "Arduous March," the forced march. They are now dynamically stepping up the general march for the Songun revolution to build a great prosperous powerful nation in the revolutionary soldier spirit based on the above-said spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are fully displaying this noble sense of revolutionary moral obligation in devoting themselves to the work to translate the desire of the revolutionary forerunners to see a rich and powerful country into brilliant reality on this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The noble spiritual and moral traits of the Korean people making energetic endeavors to win the victory of Korean-style socialism and build a great prosperous powerful nation under the uplifted banner of Songun clearly testify to the truth of history that a great leader makes his people great.

U.S. "War on Terrorism" Again Proves Failure This Year 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 26 (KCNA) -- The U.S. "war on terrorism" has brought nothing but an evil cycle of terrorism and the ensuing disorder and mayhem in different parts of the world, observes Rodong Sinmun Wednesday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "anti-terrorism war" has become a root cause of "terror-phobia" and bloodshed in different regions of the world, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Since the outset of the year, car bombings and other armed and terrorist attacks took place in Iraq in an unbroken chain, claiming huge casualties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In Afghanistan the number of suicide bomb attacks in the first eight months of the year showed an increase of approximately 70 percent as compared with that in the same period last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Two bombs went off in a city near Islamabad on September 4, killing at least 24 and wounding 66. A suicide bombing in an army barrack on September 13 killed 15 government troops. In Turkey shops and other places were targets of bomb attacks and in Lebanon several law-makers, public figures and civilians were killed by terrorist attacks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In Algeria a car bombing in August was followed by another bomb attack targeted against its president on September 6. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In several European countries bomb attacks, attempted suicide bombings and others have given rise to socio-political chaos, throwing people into uneasiness and terror. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The death toll of the U.S. soldiers in Iraq since the start of the war reached nearly 4,000 and the number of the wounded tens of thousands. More than 40,000 U.S. soldiers who were dispatched to Iraq are suffering from mental diseases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is just part of the catastrophic consequences caused by the U.S. "war on terrorism" for aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All facts clearly prove the injustice and failure of the U.S. "war on terrorism", the article says, urging the U.S. to stop the "war" for aggression and hegemony rebuffed worldwide and drop its ambition to dominate the world.

DPRK's Significant Anniversaries Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 26 (KCNA) -- Lectures, friendly meetings, book, photo and handicraft exhibitions and film shows were held in Uganda, Ethiopia, Laos, Bulgaria and Indonesia on Dec. 17 and 18 to commemorate the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of Kim Jong Suk, an anti-Japanese war hero. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venues of the events were famous works of the peerlessly great persons, photos showing their immortal feats, books and photos introducing Songun Korea and handicrafts associated with wisdom and skills of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean films "The Brilliant History of the Great Leadership" and "The 75th Anniversary of the Heroic Korean People's Army" were appreciated at the film shows. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the events were personages from different social standings and popular masses in the above-said countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The head of the Juche Idea Study Group of the Department of Teacher Education and Expansion of Chambogo University in Uganda in his lecture noted with high appreciation that Kim Jong Il shaped the great Songun policy on the basis of his deep insight into the law-governed process for accomplishing the cause of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Ethiopian Youth Study Group of the Juche Idea said in his lecture that Kim Jong Suk devotedly safeguarded President Kim Il Sung during the anti-Japanese war, registering distinguished feats in the modern history of Korea. Her immortal exploits will shine forever with the august name of Kim Jong Il, he stressed.

Feats of Peerlessly Great Persons Lauded
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 26 (KCNA) -- Saber Ballul, department head of the Faculty of Politics of University of Damascus of Syria released a statement on December 18 on the occasions of the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office  as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly praised Kim Jong Il for having pursued the unique Songun politics, developing the KPA into an army strong in idea and faith, invincible revolutionary armed forces fully prepared in military technique and a matchless army which is high in the sense of organization and discipline and has formed a perfect harmonious whole with the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He lauded Kim Jong Suk as a great mother who gave birth to and brought up Kim Jong Il in the crucible of the anti-Japanese war and as an anti-Japanese woman commander possessed of outstanding strategy and wisdom, matchless bravery, the marksmanship of never missing any target, high organizational skill and great magnanimity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Suk, having warm love for the country and the nation and ardent comradeship, defended President Kim Il Sung at the risk of her life after becoming herself a shield for him and performed immortal exploits in the struggle for the independence of Korea and the freedom and liberation of the people, giving unforgettable impressions to the younger generation, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He paid highest tribute to Kim Jong Suk, noting that she set a great example for progressive humankind to follow.

Kim Jong Il recibe regalos y cartas de Ano Nuevo de entidades rusas
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 26 de diciembre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il recibio presentes y cartas de Ano Nuevo que en ocasion del aniversario 16 de su nombramiento como Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea y del Ano Nuevo, le dirigieran el Conjunto de Danza Academica Nacional "Beriozka" N. S. Nadezhdina y el Conjunto de Danza Folclorica Academica Nacional Moiseyev, de Rusia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La subdirectora de la primera entidad, Tarasov, y la directora de la segunda, Scherbakova, los entregaron el dia 21 al embajador extraordinario y plenipotenciario coreano en Rusia.

Kim Jong Il recibe felicitacion de extranjeros en Corea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 26 de diciembre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il recibio los cestos de flores y cartas de felicitacion que en ocasion del Ano Nuevo del 97 (2008) de la Era Juche, le dirigieran el Cuerpo de Consejeros Economicos y Comerciales y los funcionarios encargados de asuntos culturales y de amistad de las embajadas de varios paises en Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El consejero comercial cubano y jefe del citado cuerpo, Enrique Gomez Soler, y el consejero pakistani, Muhammad Saeed Khan, los entregaron por separado el dia 26 a los funcionarios coreanos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Este segundo lo hizo en representacion de los funcionarios encargados de asuntos culturales y de amistad.

Rodong Sinmun critica a los belicistas japoneses 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 26 de diciembre (ATCC) -- Ahora, el Ministerio de Defensa de Japon trata de desarrollar el caza stealth de fabricacion nacional.  Y en los ultimos dias en cooperacion con las tropas norteamericanas realizo por primera vez la prueba antimisil en el buque Aegis "Gongo" cargado del cohete antimisil "SM-3". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ya se emplazo el cohete el antimisil "Patriot" "PAC-3" de lanzamiento terrestre en las bases norteamericanas en Japon. Con ello entro en la etapa de practica el plan de Japon de establecer el sistema antimisiles para interceptar por dos etapas el misil balistico. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esta conducta temeraria de los militaristas japoneses tiende a acarrear la nueva guerra fria y la carrera armamentista y a aumentar el peligro de la guerra en la region del Nordeste Asiatico. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Asi senala el periodico Rodong Sinmun en un comentario individual del dia 26 y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por medio de su incorporacion y cooperacion activa con las maniobras de EE.UU. de establecer el sistema antimisiles, los reaccionarios japoneses tratan de lograr el proposito estrategico de establecer el independiente sistema antimisiles, tomar la heguemonia militar en Asia y de realizar a toda costa su ambicion de nueva agresion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@So pretexto de hacer frente a la "amenaza de misiles" de alguien en los ultimos dias, ellos invierten enormes fondos para el estudio, el desarrollo y el ejercicio de defensa antimisil conjunto Japon-EE.UU. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por lo tanto, la reciente prueba antimisil de Japon deviene un nuevo paso peligroso en las maniobras de establecimiento del sistema antimisiles y de conversion en la potencia militar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los reaccionarios japoneses deben tener presente de que al seguir actuando asi en lugar de sacar serias lecciones de la historia volveran a morder el polvo de derrota.
